<p class="">Is the Prime Minister aware that more than 300 people of various nationalities suffered physical damage from radioactivity after the experiments last spring, and that dangerously radioactive fish were caught in the Pacific three months later? In the light of these facts, will the Prime Minister reconsider the proposal made by my right hon. and learned Friend the Member for Rowley Regis and Tipton (Mr. A. Henderson) that tests should be <span id="1040" class="column-number" data-column-number="1040"></span> suspended while the United Nations consider the abolition of atomic weapons?</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
